    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Recovery vs retention \u2014 three reference instances",
      "id": 12,
      "datasource": null,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 9,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 19
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "The panels above are the **operational** contract (serve primary, fall back to baseline, never 5xx). The **evaluative** governance \u2014 promotion gates + recovery/retention \u2014 is computed offline (`make recovery-sweep`, `make example-tabular`, `make example-embedding`).\n\n| instance | recovery @ high drift | retention @ high drift | dual gate |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Text \u00b7 AG News | 0.930 | 0.787 | **FAIL** |\n| Tabular \u00b7 Adult | 0.779 | 0.728 | **FAIL** |\n| Embeddings \u00b7 20 News | **1.000** | **0.606** | **FAIL** |\n\n**Recovery \u2260 safety.** A candidate can fully recover the drifted task (embeddings: recovery \u2248 1.0) yet be refused promotion because retention \u2014 performance on the *original* distribution \u2014 has fallen below the forgetting floor. The forgetting-aware gate is what catches this."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Multi-layer drift detection \u2014 benchmark scorecard",
      "id": 13,
      "datasource": null,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 9,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 19
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "Drift signals run as a batch monitor (`make drift`, `make benchmark`); they are not live Prometheus series. Measured over 5 seeds (`benchmarks/results.json`):\n\n| detector | precision | recall | F1 | FPR |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| PSI \u00b7 length | 1.00 | 0.29 | 0.44 | 0.00 |\n| Domain classifier \u00b7 semantic | 1.00 | 0.57 | 0.73 | 0.00 |\n| **Composite** | 1.00 | **0.71** | **0.83** | 0.00 |\n\nThe domain classifier catches the semantic drift PSI is structurally blind to \u2014 recall **0.29 \u2192 0.71 at zero false positives**. Detection triggers a retrain; the score-based gate (above) decides promotion \u2014 the two stay decoupled."
      }
    }
